</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[270,1103,547,1235]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[296,490,547,568]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Instar I. Colour.</emphasis>
Head dorsally with a pattern of light­brown and paleyellow areas; head appendages grey to brown. Thorax and abdomen grey. Legs, urogomphi and ventral body surface pale brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[880,940,601,622]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[957,1044,601,622]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[293,327,1297,1316]" captionTargetBox="[272,1098,237,1275]" captionTargetId="figure-12@10.[270,1102,234,1277]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 1. Dorsal surface of the head of instar I larvae of three species of Ilybius Erichson. A I. biguttulus, B I. discedens, C I. pleuriticus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4900143" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4900143/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). HL 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[270,290,626,648]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">5</emphasis>
<quantity box="[298,396,628,649]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.07" pageId="4" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="1.07">1.07 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[461,481,626,648]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">5</emphasis>
<quantity box="[489,588,628,649]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="0.93">0.93 mm</quantity>
. Sides of head parallel. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[846,898,627,648]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[914,980,628,649]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[293,327,766,785]" captionTargetBox="[271,1101,235,745]" captionTargetId="figure-14@12.[270,1102,234,746]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 3. Ilybius biguttulus. Instar I, right legs, anterior and posterior aspects." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4900149" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4900149/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Tibia and tarsus of each leg with ventral spinulae. Femora AV series with spinulae; PV series with two proximal setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[601,710,681,702]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[724,809,681,702]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[291,325,1550,1569]" captionTargetBox="[273,1097,236,1529]" captionTargetId="figure-11@11.[270,1100,234,1530]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 2. Last three abdominal segments and urogomphi, dorsal aspect, of instar I larvae of three species of Ilybius Erichson. A I. biguttulus, B I. discedens, C I. pleuriticus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4900147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4900147/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). LAS 0.5 times UT. Siphon long (SI/LAS 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[423,443,706,728]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">5</emphasis>
.41). Terga 1–7 with dark spiniform setae; each tergum with two dorsal and two ventral submedial and one lateral setae on each side. Sterna 1–3 with two small pale submedial setae; sterna 4–7 with two dark submedial spiniform setae, other small setae present but not prominent. Urogomphus with U4 and U3 spiniform and pale, U3 short (length of U4/length of U3 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1013,1033,813,835]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">5</emphasis>
0.51), U2 setiform and elongate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="40" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[270,1103,547,1235]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[296,493,867,888]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Instar III. Colour</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[508,593,868,889]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="14.[293,327,1406,1425]" captionTargetBox="[273,1099,235,1385]" captionTargetId="figure-12@14.[270,1102,234,1386]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 6. Dorsal body surface of instar III larvae of three species of Ilybius Erichson. A I. biguttulus, B I. discedens, C I. pleuriticus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4900159" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4900159/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
). Head with distinct dark brown and pale yellow areas. Body dorsally brown to grey with lateral and sub­lateral pale spots on each segment. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[433,493,921,942]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[511,600,921,942]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[291,325,1347,1366]" captionTargetBox="[273,1097,236,1325]" captionTargetId="figure-12@15.[270,1100,234,1327]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 7. Dorsal body surface of head of instar III larvae of three species of Ilybius Erichson. A I. biguttulus, B I. discedens, C I. pleuriticus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4900161" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4900161/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). HL 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[667,687,920,942]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">5</emphasis>
<quantity box="[698,798,921,942]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.09" pageId="4" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="2.09">2.09 mm</quantity>
, HW 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[867,887,920,942]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">5</emphasis>
<quantity box="[898,999,921,942]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.89" pageId="4" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="1.89">1.89 mm</quantity>
. Sides of head parallel. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[422,474,947,968]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Legs</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[491,557,948,969]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[293,327,585,604]" captionTargetBox="[271,1101,235,564]" captionTargetId="figure-14@16.[270,1102,234,565]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 8. Ilybius biguttulus. Instar III, right legs, anterior and posterior aspects." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4900165" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4900165/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Femora with secondary dorsal spines as follows: profemur four to six; mesofemur—four to five; metafemur five to seven; femora with spinulae in AV series. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[627,736,1001,1022]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[754,856,1001,1022]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="18.[293,326,1067,1086]" captionTargetBox="[274,1097,235,1043]" captionTargetId="figure-12@18.[273,1100,234,1047]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig. 11. Last two abdominal segments and urogomphi, dorsal aspect, of instar III larvae of three species of Ilybius Erichson. A I. biguttulus, B I. discedens, C I. pleuriticus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4900173" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4900173/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). LAS 0.69 times UT. Abdomen with dorsal surface bearing numerous spiniform setae; primary setae setiform.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="40" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[270,1103,547,1235]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[296,392,1081,1102]" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Ecology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[400,586,1081,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Dytiscidae" genus="Ilybius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biguttulus">
<emphasis box="[400,586,1081,1102]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="40">Ilybius biguttulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
adults and larvae were collected in small pools and along the edges of larger ponds. In all cases they occurred among the aquatic vegetation and in sites where water levels were variable. Collected female adults laid eggs that hatched in late September. Collected instar I larvae were found in late August and early September. These records support the life history proposed by Hicks and Larson (1995) for this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
